WEEK 8 – JENKINS AUTOMATION
Complete Instructions (Ready to Copy-Paste)

---------------------------------------------------
A. OVERALL TASK FOR WEEK 8
---------------------------------------------------
1) Set up Jenkins and required tools.
2) Create AUTOMATION for:
   - Maven Java project (MavenJava_Build + MavenJava_Test + pipeline view).
   - Maven Web project (MavenWeb_Build + MavenWeb_Test + MavenWeb_Deploy + pipeline view + Tomcat deploy).
3) Run all pipelines and verify they are successful (green).
4) Take CLEAR screenshots of all important steps (jobs, builds, pipeline, Tomcat output).
5) Answer all Jenkins theory questions given in the document.
6) Upload your screenshots and question answers as instructed.

---------------------------------------------------
C. MAVEN JAVA AUTOMATION – DETAILED STEPS
---------------------------------------------------

C1. OPEN JENKINS
1) Open browser → Go to: http://localhost:8080
2) Login to Jenkins.

C2. CREATE FREESTYLE PROJECT: MavenJava_Build
1) Jenkins dashboard → Click "New Item".
2) Enter name: MavenJava_Build
3) Choose: Freestyle project
4) Click "OK".

C3. CONFIGURE MavenJava_Build JOB
1) Add description: Java Build demo
2) Go to "Source Code Management" → Select "Git"
   - Paste your repo URL
   - Branch: */main OR */master
3) Go to "Build"
   - Add build step → Invoke top-level Maven targets → Goals: clean
   - Add build step → Invoke top-level Maven targets → Goals: install
4) Go to "Post-build Actions"
   - Archive the artifacts → Files: **/*
   - Build other projects → MavenJava_Test → Trigger: Only if build is stable
5) Click Apply → Save

C4. CREATE FREESTYLE PROJECT: MavenJava_Test
1) New Item → MavenJava_Test → Freestyle → OK

C5. CONFIGURE MavenJava_Test
1) Add description: Test demo
2) Build Environment → Tick: Delete workspace before build starts
3) Build:
   - Add build step → Copy artifacts from another project
     - Project name: MavenJava_Build
     - Build: Stable build only
     - Artifacts: **/*
   - Add build step → Invoke top-level Maven targets
     - Goals: test
4) Post-build Actions:
   - Archive the artifacts → Files: **/*
5) Apply → Save

C6. CREATE PIPELINE VIEW: MavenJava_Pipeline
1) Dashboard → + New View
2) Name: MavenJava_Pipeline
3) View Type: Build Pipeline View
4) OK
5) Pipeline Flow:
   - Layout: Based on upstream/downstream relationship
   - Initial job: MavenJava_Build
6) Apply → Save

C7. RUN PIPELINE & VERIFY
1) Open MavenJava_Pipeline view
2) Click "Run"
3) Verify pipeline turns green:
   - Build success
   - Test success
4) Check console output
5) Take screenshots of:
   - Jobs
   - Build & test success
   - Pipeline (green)

---------------------------------------------------
D. MAVEN WEB AUTOMATION – DETAILED STEPS
---------------------------------------------------

D1. OPEN JENKINS
1) Visit: http://localhost:8080

D2. CREATE JOB: MavenWeb_Build
1) New Item → MavenWeb_Build → Freestyle → OK

D3. CONFIGURE MavenWeb_Build
1) Description: Web Build demo
2) Source Code Management:
   - Git repo URL
   - Branch */main OR */master
3) Build:
   - clean
   - install
4) Post-build actions:
   - Archive artifacts: **/*
   - Build other projects → MavenWeb_Test (Only if stable)
5) Apply → Save

D4. CREATE JOB: MavenWeb_Test
1) New Item → MavenWeb_Test → Freestyle → OK

D5. CONFIGURE MavenWeb_Test
1) Description: Test demo
2) Build environment → Delete workspace before build
3) Build:
   - Copy artifacts from MavenWeb_Build → Stable → **/*
   - Invoke Maven targets → test
4) Post-build:
   - Archive artifacts: **/*
   - Build MavenWeb_Deploy
5) Apply → Save

D6. CREATE JOB: MavenWeb_Deploy
1) New Item → MavenWeb_Deploy → Freestyle → OK

D7. CONFIGURE MAVENWEB_DEPLOY
1) Description: Web Code Deployment
2) Build Environment → Delete workspace before build
3) Build:
   - Copy artifacts from MavenWeb_Test → Stable → **/*
4) Post-build actions:
   - Deploy WAR/EAR to container
     - WAR/EAR File: **/*.war
     - Context path: Webpath
     - Container: Tomcat 9.x remote
       - URL: https://localhost:8085/
       - Credentials: admin / 1234
5) Apply → Save

D8. CREATE PIPELINE VIEW: MavenWeb_Pipeline
1) Dashboard → + → Build Pipeline View
2) Name: MavenWeb_Pipeline → OK
3) Initial job: MavenWeb_Build
4) Apply → Save

D9. RUN WEB PIPELINE & VERIFY
1) Open MavenWeb_Pipeline
2) Run pipeline
3) Verify:
   - Build → Test → Deploy (all green)
4) Open Tomcat manager:
   - https://localhost:8085/
   - Login: admin / 1234
5) Click /webpath & confirm app runs
6) Take screenshots

